parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Passenger Airbag and Seatbelt Warning Light Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger airbag and seatbelt warning light system can lead to the deactivation of the passenger airbag, increasing the risk of personal injury in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The passenger airbag and seatbelt warning lights are illuminated
the passenger airbag is not detected when a passenger is seated
and the passenger airbag indicator is off or not engaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Takata airbag recall can lead to the rupture of the airbag inflator, causing serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
and the airbag did not deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the electronic steering wheel lock can cause the vehicle to not start, and the steering wheel to lock, which can leave the driver stranded and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: The yellow or red steering wheel lock warning light appears on the dashboard
and the vehicle may experience intermittent electronic outages.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to lose power steering, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: the power steering warning light appears on the dashboard
and the vehicle may experience intermittent electronic outages.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the belt tensioner can cause the serpentine belt to slip off, leading to engine failure, which can cause accidents.
